{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c97d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"511"},"text":"§ 511.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Imposition of tax on unrelated business income of charitable, etc., organizations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c97e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Charitable, etc., organizations taxable at corporation rates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c97f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Imposition of tax","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is hereby imposed for each taxable year on the unrelated business taxable income (as defined in section 512) of every organization described in paragraph (2) a tax computed as provided in section 11. In making such computation for purposes of this section, the term “taxable income” as used in section 11 shall be read as “unrelated business taxable income”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c980-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Organizations subject to tax","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c981-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Organizations described in sections 401(a) and 501(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The tax imposed by paragraph (1) shall apply in the case of any organization (other than a trust described in subsection (b) or an organization described in section 501(c)(1)) which is exempt, except as provided in this part or part II (relating to private foundations), from taxation under this subtitle by reason of section 501(a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c982-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State colleges and universities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The tax imposed by paragraph (1) shall apply in the case of any college or university which is an agency or instrumentality of any government or any political subdivision thereof, or which is owned or operated by a government or any political subdivision thereof, or by any agency or instrumentality of one or more governments or political subdivisions. Such tax shall also apply in the case of any corporation wholly owned by one or more such colleges or universities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c983-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Tax on charitable, etc., trusts","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c984-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Imposition of tax","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is hereby imposed for each taxable year on the unrelated business taxable income of every trust described in paragraph (2) a tax computed as provided in section 1(e). In making such computation for purposes of this section, the term “taxable income” as used in section 1 shall be read as “unrelated business taxable income” as defined in section 512.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c985-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Charitable, etc., trusts subject to tax","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The tax imposed by paragraph (1) shall apply in the case of any trust which is exempt, except as provided in this part or part II (relating to private foundations), from taxation under this subtitle by reason of section 501(a) and which, if it were not for such exemption, would be subject to subchapter J (sec. 641 and following, relating to estates, trusts, beneficiaries, and decedents).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c986-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Special rule for section 501(c)(2) corporations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"If a corporation described in section 501(c)(2)—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c987-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" pays any amount of its net income for a taxable year to an organization exempt from taxation under section 501(a) (or which would pay such an amount but for the fact that the expenses of collecting its income exceed its income), and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c988-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s511/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such corporation and such organization file a consolidated return for the taxable year,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"such corporation shall be treated, for purposes of the tax imposed by subsection (a), as being organized and operated for the same purposes as such organization, in addition to the purposes described in section 501(c)(2).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id43b3c989-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/169"},"text":"68A Stat. 169","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/667/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–667, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-07-14"},"text":"July 14, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/535"},"text":"74 Stat. 535","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/352/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–352, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-02-02"},"text":"Feb. 2, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/4"},"text":"80 Stat. 4","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/tI/s121/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, title I, § 121(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":"–(3), title III, § 301(b)(8), title VIII, § 803(d)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/536"},"text":"83 Stat. 536","children":[],"tail":", 585, 684; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/30/tI/s101/d/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–30, title I, § 101(d)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-05-23"},"text":"May 23, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/133"},"text":"91 Stat. 133","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/tIII/s301/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600, title III, § 301(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 421(e)(3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2821"},"text":"92 Stat. 2821","children":[],"tail":", 2876; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248/tII/s201/d/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248, title II, § 201(d)(5)","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 201(c)(5), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-03"},"text":"Sept. 3, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/419"},"text":"96 Stat. 419","children":[],"tail":", renumbered § 201(d)(5), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/448/tIII/s306/a/1/A/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–448, title III, § 306(a)(1)(A)(i)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-12"},"text":"Jan. 12, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2400"},"text":"96 Stat. 2400","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/tI/s1007/g/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, title I, § 1007(g)(6)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3435"},"text":"102 Stat. 3435","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id43b3c98a-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id43b3c98b-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id43b3c98c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (d) which read as follows: “"},{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Tax Preferences","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Organizations taxable at corporate rates","children":[],"tail":".—If an organization is subject to tax on unrelated business taxable income pursuant to subsection (a), the tax imposed by section 56 shall apply to such organizations with respect to items of tax preference which enter into the computation of unrelated business taxable income in the same manner as section 56 applies to corporations."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Organizations taxable as trusts","children":[],"tail":".—If an organization is subject to tax on unrelated business taxable income pursuant to subsection (b), the taxes imposed by section 55 shall apply to such organization with respect to items of tax preference which enter into the computation of unrelated business taxable income.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 55” for “section 55 and section 56 (as the case may be)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s301/b/5/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600, § 301(b)(5)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a tax” for “a normal tax and a surtax”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s301/b/5/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600, § 301(b)(5)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “tax” for “taxes” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s421/e/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600, § 421(e)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions relating to organizations taxable at corporate rates and organizations taxable as trusts, for provisions relating to imposition of the tax imposed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s56"},"text":"section 56 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to an organization subject to tax under this section for tax preferences computed in unrelated business taxable income."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1977—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/30"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–30","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 1(e)” for “section 1(d)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1969—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s121/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 121(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", removed reference, in heading, to pars. (2), (3), (5), (6), (14)(B), (C), and (17) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s501/c"},"text":"section 501(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":", and, in text, struck out exemptions to churches, conventions, or associations of churches, from the imposition of tax on their unrelated business income, made corporations organized under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s501/c/1"},"text":"section 501(c)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":" (i.e. organized under Acts of Congress), exempt from such tax, but made all such exemptions subservient to the exceptions in part II and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s501/a"},"text":"section 501(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s803/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 803(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted section 1(d) for section 1 in reference to section under which the computation of the tax dealing with the imposition of tax on the unrelated business taxable income of trusts, is computed."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s121/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 121(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", pluralized “trust” in heading and in text made the imposition of tax on the unrelated business income of exempt trusts subject to provisions of part II, and, for purposes of determining trusts exempt from taxation, substituted reference to section 501(a) for reference to “section 501(c)(3) or (17) or section 401(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s121/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 121(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c). Former subsec. (c), covering the effective date, was struck out."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s301/b/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 301(b)(8)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1966—Subsec. (a)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/352"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–352","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(14)(B) or (C),” after “(6),” in heading and in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1960—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/667/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–667, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", included organizations described in section 501(c)(17) within subpar. (A)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/667/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–667, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted a reference to section 501(c)(17)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id43b3c98d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43b3c98e-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1988 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647","children":[],"tail":" effective, except as otherwise provided, as if included in the provision of the Tax Reform Act of 1986, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":", to which such amendment relates, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/s1019/a"},"text":"section 1019(a) of Pub. L. 100–647","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43b3c98f-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1982 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":" applicable to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1982","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/248/s201/e/1"},"text":"section 201(e)(1) of Pub. L. 97–248","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s5"},"text":"section 5 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43b3c990-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by section 301(b)(5)(A), (B) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–600","children":[],"tail":" applicable to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s301/c"},"text":"section 301(c) of Pub. L. 95–600","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s11"},"text":"section 11 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s421/e/3"},"text":"section 421(e)(3) of Pub. L. 95–600","children":[],"tail":" applicable to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/600/s421/g"},"text":"section 421(g) of Pub. L. 95–600","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s5"},"text":"section 5 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43b3c991-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1977 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/30"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–30","children":[],"tail":" applicable to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1976","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/30/s106/a"},"text":"section 106(a) of Pub. L. 95–30","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43b3c992-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1969 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/tI/s121/g"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, title I, § 121(g)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/549"},"text":"83 Stat. 549","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2095"},"text":"100 Stat. 2095","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/99/514/s2"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section and sections 48, 501, 502, 503, 512 to 514, 681, 801, 810, 1443, 1504, and 7605 of this title] (other than by subsections (b)(3) and (e) [enacting sections 277 and 6050 of this title]) shall apply to taxable years beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1969","children":[],"tail":". The amendments made by subsection (b)(3) [enacting "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s277"},"text":"section 277 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply to taxable years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1970","children":[],"tail":". The amendments made by subsection (e) [enacting "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s6050"},"text":"section 6050 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall apply with respect to transfers of property after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1969","children":[],"tail":". Where an organization makes a bargain purchase of property before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-10-09"},"text":"October 9, 1969","children":[],"tail":", which is subject to a mortgage which was placed on the property more than 5 years before the purchase, and the organization paid the seller a total amount no greater than the amount of the seller’s cost (including attorneys’ fees) directly related to the transfer of such property to the organization (but in any event no more than 10 percent of the value of the seller’s equity in the property), the indebtedness secured by such mortgage shall not be treated, notwithstanding the amendments made by subsection (d)(1) [amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s514"},"text":"section 514 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], as acquisition indebtedness for purposes of section 514(c)(1) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 [formerly I.R.C. 1954] during a 